OL,5,F"Right through July and August we were
OL,6,Fthe guard ship and did our duties
OL,7,Fescorting hospital ships and the like."
OL,9,FMr Ford was on board one day in August
OL,10,Fwhen Fratton was fired on by a midget
OL,11,Fsubmarine and sunk off the Normandy
OL,12,Fcoast.
OL,14,FHe said: "I had been on guard duty on
OL,15,Fthe gun platform. Oerlikons were very
OL,16,Fcapable armaments for low-flying
OL,17,Faircraft and the like. There was a
OL,18,Fterrific explosion.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
